Reasoning: The paper discusses the history and current state of AI research in games, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also discusses the fairness of competition between humans and machines in game benchmarks, which relates to game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches on the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect of game benchmarks and the potential for misrepresentation and exaggeration, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
